 is the worlds thirdlargest supplier of enterprise resource planning software behind oracle and sap the largest supplier to small businesses and has  million customers worldwide it has offices in  countries the company is the patron of the sage gateshead music venue in gateshead sage is listed on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index contents  history   to    to    to present  operations  financial information  products  sponsorships  see also  references  external links historyedit  to edit the company was founded by david goldman paul muller and graham wylie in  in newcastle to develop estimating and accounting software for small businesses a student at newcastle university graham wylie took a summer job with an accountancy firm funded by a government small business grant to write software to help their record keeping this became the basis for sage line  next hired by david goldman to write some estimating software for his printing company campbell graphics graham used the same accounting software to produce the first version of sage accounts david was so impressed that he hired graham and academic paul muller to form sage selling their software first to printing companies and then to a wider market through a network of resellers in  the company launched sage software a product for the amstrad pcw word processor which used the cpm operating system sage software sales escalated in that year from  copies a month to over  the company was first listed on the london stock exchange in  in  paul walker was appointed chief executive in  sages professional accountants division was established in  sage entered ftse  and launched a dedicated irish division based in dublin as well as its ebusiness strategy in that same year the uk acquisition of tetra saw sage enter the midrange business software market  to edit the sage gateshead music venue located on the banks of the river tyne is named after the company in  sage shares were named best performing share of the s in the uk business press in  sage acquired interact commerce inc and entered the crmcontact management market and in  sage won business of the year in national business awards also that year sage sponsored the new music centre in gateshead for £m  now known as the sage gateshead  the largest ever uk artsbusiness sponsorship sage are one of two technology stocks listed on the ftse  index in  at age  graham wylie retired with  million shares in sage worth £m he was rated britains th richest person in the  sunday times rich list tony hobson joined the sage board of directors in june  and became chairman in may   to presentedit on  april  sage announced that its ceo paul walker had indicated an interest in stepping down from his position which he had held for  years the financial times reported that his departure would lead to speculation over sages mergers and acquisitions which have been a key component to the groups growth in the past  years in an interview with the times the ceo of sages uk business stated that acquisitions are part of our dna walker was one of the longest serving ceos of a ftse company only exceeded by sir martin sorrell at wpp and tullow oils aidan heavey according to the daily mail walker is likely to have left sage with as much as £ million given his shares bonus plan and salary walker left the company on  december  on  october  guy berruyer became ceo of sage group berruyer had previously been ceo of sages mainland europe  asia operations on  february  sage announced that accelkkr intended to buy sage nonprofit solutions the division of sage that produces software designed for nonprofit organisations and governmental agencies in august  sage announced that guy berruyer was to retire stephen kelly the uk government’s former chief operating officer became group ceo in november  in july  sage announced that it would purchase intacct for m operationsedit founded and headquartered in newcastle upon tyne united kingdom the company initially grew organically but more recently has grown primarily through acquisitions in  the companys new headquarters was completed in the great park area of newcastle upon tyne the company was previously located at benton park house it now operates worldwide the companys us headquarters are in atlanta georgia the canadian headquarters are in richmond british columbia the africa middle east  australia headquarters are in johannesburg south africa and the french and continental european headquarters are in paris france sage has  million customers and  employees across the world key industry focus includes healthcare hr  payroll construction realestate transport distribution payment processing accountancy notforprofit manufacturing retail automotive distribution financial informationedit sages former logo until  financial results are as follows sept yearend £ millions                 revenue                reported growth na na na na            underlying growth na na na na            ebita na na na             pretax profit                productsedit the companys core product set can be divided into three areas accounting payroll  human capital management and payments as sage operates in a large number of countries the available product set varies and typically includes products specifically tailored for each regions nuanced legislation regarding accounting payroll and taxation sages worldwide products include sage one sage live sage x sage pay sage payments and sage people sages more regional product ranges include providex sage c accounts uk sage  accounting sage  payroll sage  pastel accounting sage  sage  sage  and sage crm sponsorshipsedit a marussia f promotional car on display in sages newcastle headquarters the sage group is a patron of the sage gateshead a tyneside music venue designed by sir norman foster the sage gateshead was completed in  at a cost of £ million and has since become a main sight on the river tyne it is primarily used as a concert venue and centre for musical education but also hosts other events including conferences in  sage funded the revival of the krypton factor television series for itv as a part of the business brain training campaign sage were the football shirt sponsor in may  for whitley bay fcs fa vase winning match for the  formula one season sage were an official supplier for the marussia f team and for the  and  seasons sage logos were placed on the car see alsoedit companies portal comparison of accounting software comparison of crm systems list of erp software packages referencesedit  a b c d e annual report  pdf the sage group plc retrieved  april    competitive profile the sage group plc archived from the original on  november  retrieved  september    sage investor relations website retrieved  march    arts funding in recession incorporated society of musicians retrieved  september    a b c d e history sage retrieved  october    a b vaughanadams liz  april  sage founder retires at  to get married and enjoy his £m fortune the independent on sunday london retrieved  march    sage buys tetra london the independent  march  retrieved  october    accounting for sages move on tetra the register retrieved  march    sage looks risky in an uncertain business climate dead link  sage buys interact commerce  business of the year  red hot curry  october  archived from the original on  april  retrieved  november    a b software sages of newcastle global technology forum  april  retrieved  november    ftse  fact sheet ftse  march  retrieved  april    directors biographies sage group plc archived from the original on  january  retrieved  january    walker to step down as sage chief executive financial times retrieved  march    business big shot paul stobart london the times  april  retrieved  november    sage ceo paul walker to stand down after  years at company london daily mail  april  retrieved  april    duke simon  april  sage chief paul walker is set to exit with £m london daily mail retrieved